
* ability to pass compiled tasklang programs to LOAD_TASK
    * HEAP is easy, but CODE requires converting some instruction arguments
      to CODE pointers, HEAP pointers, and builtin routine pointers
    * Builtin routine pointers require a table, like avr-gcc's __vectors.
      In avr/sfr_defs.h, there is:

        #define _VECTOR(N) __vector_ ## N

      Also look at /usr/lib/avr/lib/ldscripts/.
      There is stuff like:

          .text   :
          {
            *(.vectors)
            KEEP(*(.vectors))

      ...but where is the __vectors symbol I see in objdump output defined?..
      Ah ha, look here:

        ~/repos/avr-libc$ ack __vectors
        crt1/gcrt1.S
        187:	.if (. - __vectors < _VECTORS_SIZE)
        195:	.global	__vectors
        196:	.func	__vectors
        197:__vectors:
        359:	.set	__vector_default, __vectors
        422:	ldi	r16, hh8(pm(__vectors))


* ability to run programs
    * implement threaded code, the builtins
    * do multitasking from the very start: a timer interrupt which does
      context switching

* resource queues
